QUESTION:
Input: board = 
[["5","3",".",".","7",".",".",".","."]
,["6",".",".","1","9","5",".",".","."]
,[".","9","8",".",".",".",".","6","."]
,["8",".",".",".","6",".",".",".","3"]
,["4",".",".","8",".","3",".",".","1"]
,["7",".",".",".","2",".",".",".","6"]
,[".","6",".",".",".",".","2","8","."]
,[".",".",".","4","1","9",".",".","5"]
,[".",".",".",".","8",".",".","7","9"]]
Output: true
SOLUTION:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Why (quick intuition):
The board size is fixed (9×9), so even though you loop, it’s always a constant amount of work.
The boolean arrays are size 9 → constant space.

If it were an N×N Sudoku, then: Time: O(N²) Space: O(N)
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(1)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(1)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
->Create a boolean variable to go row wise to check if the number is already filled.
->Create the same for column wise values.
->then to check 3*3 for that you have to block/3*3 -> block/3*3+3 and block%3*3 -> block%3*3+3
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public boolean isValidSudoku(char[][] board) {
        if(board==null || board.length!=9 || board[0].length!=9)return false;
        for(int i=0;i<9;i++){
            boolean []b=new boolean[9];
            for(int j=0;j<9;j++){
                if(board[i][j]!= '.'){
                if(b[(int)board[i][j]-'1'])return false;
                b[(int)board[i][j]-'1']=true;
            }
            }
        }
        for(int j=0;j<9;j++){
            boolean []b=new boolean[9];
            for(int i=0;i<9;i++){
                if(board[i][j]!= '.'){
                if(b[(int)board[i][j]-'1'])return false;
                b[(int)board[i][j]-'1']=true;
            }}
        }
        for(int block=0;block<9;block++){
            boolean []b=new boolean[9];
            for(int i=block/3*3;i<block/3*3+3;i++){
                for(int j=block%3*3;j<block%3*3+3;j++){
                     if(board[i][j]!= '.'){
                if(b[(int)board[i][j]-'1'])return false;
                b[(int)board[i][j]-'1']=true;
            }
            }
        }
    }
    return true;
    }
}
